            Basic Command
    1. to create project - ng new project-name / ng new project-name --routing
    2. to run a project - ng serve / ng serve --open / ng serve --o
    3. to create component - ng g c component-name
    4. to create service - ng g s service-name

            Basic Concepts

    1. Component -to create ( html, css, ts file) root component - Appcomponent
    
    2. Module - to aff libraries to the project - root module - Appmodule
    
    3. Data Binding - data sharing between html and ts
        3.1 One way binding
            3.1.1       component to view
                3.1.1.1 String Interpolation: syntax- {{variable-name}}
                3.1.1.2 Property binding: syntax - [attribute] = "variable-name" 
            3.1.2 view to component
                3.1.2.1 Event Binding - (event)="function-call()"
                3.1.2.1 Event Binding using $event - (event)="function-call($event)"
                3.1.2.3 Template referencing variable - syntax: #variable-name 
        3.2 Two way binding 
            3.2 Using ngModel - Import FormsModule in Appmodule, syntax: [{ngModel}]="variable-name"
    
    4. To setup path for a component : defined in App Routing 
    syntax: {path:'',component:componentClassName}     
    
    5. Dependency Injection - to share data between classses

    6. Angular Services - for re-use data

    7. ngSubmit - to submit entire form syntax: (ngSubmit)="function-call"

    8. Angular Forms

        8.1 Template Driven Forms - first design html

        8.2 Model Driven Forms - fist create model in ts

            8.2.1   Reactive Forms - Add Validation: Import ReactiveFormsModule
                        -   form group - FormBuilder dependency inject, form array, form control

